---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — bellsoftware" description="About this site." active="about">
  <article>
    <header class="article-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>
    <Prose>
      <p>
        I'm a senior software engineer at Getty Images, where I lead the <strong>SRE guild</strong> and work on
        <strong>platform reliability</strong>, <strong>frontend infrastructure</strong>, and migrating legacy <code>Rails</code> systems to
        <code>Nest.js</code>/<code>TypeScript</code>. Day to day: <strong>SLOs</strong>, alerting, bot mitigation, fraud prevention, and
        reducing <strong>tech debt</strong> across <strong>microfrontends</strong> at scale.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside work, I build autonomous AI agent systems: <strong>multi-agent architectures</strong> with
        task-specialized <strong>subagents</strong>, local LLM inference, and tool-using agents wired into real
        workflows. I'm interested in how <strong>agentic systems</strong> change the shape of software: what becomes
        a skill vs. a service, how context flows between agents, and where determinism still
        matters.
      </p>
      <p>
        I came to engineering non-traditionally. International studies and philosophy degree,
        career transition bootcamp, then ten years building up from there. But I was already
        thinking this way before the switch: I taught myself <code>Ruby</code> at my old job to wrangle large
        datasets and automate the tedious parts away. I've always been drawn to making work easier
        and clearer for myself and the people around me. That instinct translates well to building systems with AI.
      </p>
    </Prose>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article {
    max-width: var(--content-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-24);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    article {
      padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-16);
    }
  }

  .article-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
  }

  .article-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .article-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    }
  }
</style>
